Taking a different tack...
From <a href="http://www.oldandsold.com/articles14/travel-363.shtml">www.oldandsold.com/articles14/travel-363.shtml</a>

&quot;The Montenegrin army began the fighting. It made an attack on the Turkish position at Podgoritza, and after a four hours' artillery engagement, forced the Turks to evacuate the heights they had occupied. The Montenegrins then attacked the fortified position of the Turks at Detchich.&quot;

So, maybe it should be Decic (or rather Dečić).  See <a href="http://www.nationmaster.com/encyclopedia/Tuzi">www.nationmaster.com/encyclopedia/Tuzi</a>
&quot;Tuzi and Malesia became a part of Montenegro some 90 years ago. Tuzi was under Ottoman (Turkish) rule as all the other Albanian and neighbouring lands. Although it was the last one that fell under Turkish rule &amp; the first one that was liberated. The first national upheaval for liberation from Turkish rule, after the death of Gjergj Kastroiti Skendernbeu, was initiated in the forests near Tuzi, in Dečić hill.&quot;
